1. Beginning with 1991, includes change in farm materials and supplies inventories.
2. Prior to 1981, inventories of auto and home supply stores are included in motor vehicle dealers.
Beginning with 1981, these inventories are included in 'other durable goods.'
Note. Estimates for nonfarm industries other than manufacturing and trade for 1986 and earlier periods
are based on the 1972 Standard Industrial Classification (SIC). Manufacturing estimates for 1981 and
earlier periods and trade estimates for 1966 and earlier periods are based on the 1972 SIC; later estimates
for these industries are based on the 1987 SIC. The resulting discontinuities are small.
Note. Chained (2009) dollar series for real change in private inventories are calculated as the period-to-period
change in chained-dollar end-of-period inventories. Quarterly changes in end-of-period inventories are
stated at annual rates. Because the formula for the chain-type quantity indexes uses weights of more
than one period, the corresponding chained-dollar estimates are usually not additive. The residual line
is the difference between the first line and the sum of the most detailed lines.
